  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Classification: Internal Use Only

    Document ID: H-73/0421-IC

    Originating
    Department / Laboratory: Cognitive Systems Research Unit


    Induction of Controlled
    Cognitive Synchrony in Human Subjects


    This study documents the controlled
    induction of prolonged unconscious states in multiple adult participants. Subjects
    were placed under pharmacologically maintained comas and sustained using standard
    ventilatory support. Neural activity was modulated via a centralized device designed
    to produce uniform cortical oscillations. Continuous monitoring was conducted
    to ensure synchronization across subjects. Data recorded includes electroencephalographic
    patterns, autonomic stability, and variance reduction in higher-order brain activity.











    One
    subject exhibited brief arrhythmic fluctuations during initial induction, resolved
    without intervention. Uniformity remained intact thereafter. Long-term effects
    remain undetermined.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 28ab9fc86e0f64bae87ca99422e30788, type: 2}
